climbs.name: Mad Dog
climbs.fa: idk some crunchy oldschool guy in lycra probably

content.description: Stand start at the right side of the wall. Fun stemming leads to a nice pinch and an exciting dyno to a good jug. Work your way up and left to finish on the ledge. Once on the ledge, continue left to exit same as "Barefoot".

climbs.name: Franzia
climbs.fa: idk some crunchy oldschool guy in lycra probably

content.description: Stand start in the center of the wall good edges below a seem. Pull up to the seem, traverse right to reach a good jug, then work your way up and left to finish on the ledge. Once on the ledge, continue left to exit same as "Barefoot".

climbs.name: Barefoot
climbs.fa: idk some crunchy oldschool guy in lycra probably

content.description:
Stand start on the far left side of the wall. Climb up trending right. From the last ledge, take the path of least resistance to the top.

 Great warm-up easy lap up the main wall. Good for getting your head in the right place for topping this slightly intimidating wall. Also, if you climb it as I did, the top of this problem can serve as your exit strategy for the other climbs on the wall.
Less steep than the neighboring "Basement Wall" which leads to slightly easier, but equally engaging climbing.
